-- Portugal’s Trade Gap Narrows as Exports Increase, Imports Falls
-- B y   J o a o   L i m a
-- 2012-10-10T10:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-10/portugal-s-trade-gap-narrows-as-exports-increase-imports-falls.html
Portugal ’s  trade deficit  narrowed in
the three months through August as exports rose and imports
fell, the country’s statistics institute said.  The trade deficit narrowed to 2.18 billion euros 
($2.8 billion) from 3.46 billion euros in the same period a year
 earlier, the Lisbon-based institute said today in an e-mailed 
report. Exports rose 10.4 percent and imports fell 1.5 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joao Lima in Lisbon at 
